  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat oven to 180°C. Lightly grease and line a deep baking tray with baking paper and set aside. In a large bowl mix together the flour, bicarbonate of soda, both sugars, salt and the cocoa powder. If there are any hard lumps of sugar break using your fingers."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In another large bowl whisk together the eggs, vanilla and soured cream. Finely chop the chocolate and dice the butter, then add both to a pot, melting over a medium heat whilst stirring until totally combined. Add the coffee granules to a jug and top up with the boiling water."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour the soured cream mix into the dry ingredients along with the coffee and melted chocolate, fold together using a large metal spoon until combined – do not over mix. Pour into the lined baking tray and pop into the oven for 50 mins to 1 hour until cooked. You can check if it's cooked or not by poking it through the centre with a skewer – if it comes out clean, the cake is ready!"
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Set aside to cool, remove from the baking tray, sprinkle with the granulated sugar and slice."
    }
  ],
